1
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:29,981
Are you okay, Mom?

2
00:01:31,489 --> 00:01:33,015
It's just a little stomach ache.

3
00:01:34,208 --> 00:01:37,088
Can you keep an eye
on the baby while I lay down?

4
00:01:37,088 --> 00:01:38,070
Yeah.

5
00:02:13,823 --> 00:02:15,961
Okay, it's okay.

6
00:02:16,287 --> 00:02:17,759
Everything's gonna be okay.

7
00:02:25,247 --> 00:02:26,523
Good night, little brother.

8
00:03:37,757 --> 00:03:39,644
Give me strength, Lords.

9
00:04:03,003 --> 00:04:05,084
- Benjamin?
- Yes.

10
00:04:05,084 --> 00:04:08,507
Something is wrong,
I need to go to the hospital.

11
00:04:08,507 --> 00:04:11,067
You can't go to the hospital,
sweetheart.

12
00:04:11,067 --> 00:04:12,212
Why not?

13
00:04:13,819 --> 00:04:16,668
It's time for the final step.

14
00:04:16,668 --> 00:04:18,577
What are you talking about?

15
00:04:40,507 --> 00:04:41,783
Elizabeth?

16
00:04:42,523 --> 00:04:44,017
Daniel?

17
00:04:45,914 --> 00:04:47,224
What's wrong?

18
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,535
9-1-1,
where is your emergency?

19
00:06:14,551 --> 00:06:16,145
Daniel.

20
00:06:21,432 --> 00:06:22,520
I'm sorry, Bryan.

21
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,632
Give me the baby, Daniel!

22
00:06:24,632 --> 00:06:25,973
It has to be finished!

23
00:06:31,383 --> 00:06:32,910
Daniel.

24
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:40,272
Daniel, it's the only way.

25
00:07:05,238 --> 00:07:06,831
For the good of us all.

26
00:07:11,062 --> 00:07:13,266
You just don't understand.

27
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,655
Where is he, Daniel!

28
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:25,876
Hello?

29
00:08:25,876 --> 00:08:27,054
Anyone home?

30
00:09:03,059 --> 00:09:04,488
Mr. Conroy.

31
00:09:26,258 --> 00:09:27,305
My God.

32
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:42,767
I was wrong.

33
00:09:44,657 --> 00:09:45,935
There's one more.

34
00:09:56,657 --> 00:09:59,697
Oh, my parents flipped when
they found out I applied out of state.

35
00:09:59,697 --> 00:10:02,609
But whatever, it's not like
they really have a say in what I do.

36
00:10:02,609 --> 00:10:03,951
Man, you're so lucky.

37
00:10:04,849 --> 00:10:06,417
I'd give anything to get outta here.

38
00:10:06,417 --> 00:10:09,232
What, Mary Mother of God
still callin' all the shots?

39
00:10:09,232 --> 00:10:13,297
She thinks colleges are, uh,
morally corrupt breeding grounds.

40
00:10:13,297 --> 00:10:14,759
Well, yeah.

41
00:10:17,553 --> 00:10:19,057
Damn it.

42
00:10:19,057 --> 00:10:20,202
Nothin' yet.

43
00:10:21,425 --> 00:10:23,056
Birthday present.

44
00:10:23,056 --> 00:10:26,024
Ah-- jealous.

45
00:10:32,528 --> 00:10:33,575
Hey.

46
00:10:34,448 --> 00:10:35,375
What?

47
00:10:36,528 --> 00:10:39,024
Hey, eventually my mom's
gonna start to notice.

48
00:10:39,024 --> 00:10:40,365
Come on, she never notices.

49
00:10:41,872 --> 00:10:43,696
She's gonna be home any minute,
so you gotta clear out.

50
00:10:43,696 --> 00:10:44,849
Why?

51
00:10:44,849 --> 00:10:46,704
Because you know I'm not
supposed to have friends over,

52
00:10:46,704 --> 00:10:47,718
especially you.

53
00:10:48,624 --> 00:10:49,572
Come on.

54
00:10:52,304 --> 00:10:53,776
Typical.

55
00:10:53,776 --> 00:10:55,215
What?

56
00:10:55,215 --> 00:10:57,743
Have you ever had a thought
that she didn't feed you?

57
00:10:57,743 --> 00:10:59,215
Uh, of course.

58
00:10:59,215 --> 00:11:01,583
Yeah, uh, let me see
your cell phone real quick.

59
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:02,831
You know I don't have one.

60
00:11:02,831 --> 00:11:04,591
Oh, right-- why is that again?

61
00:11:04,591 --> 00:11:06,860
Because they cause brain tumors.

62
00:11:08,111 --> 00:11:09,135
Bingo.

63
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:11,375
See, it's like you're
a weird little clone.

64
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:12,652
Good-bye, Scott.

65
00:11:14,735 --> 00:11:16,976
I'm gonna come back
and find you and her

66
00:11:16,976 --> 00:11:19,081
running a creepy motel
right off the Interstate, aren't I?

67
00:11:20,303 --> 00:11:22,442
Ree! Ree! Ree! Ree!

68
00:11:24,303 --> 00:11:25,612
Get a TV.

69
00:11:45,742 --> 00:11:47,246
This is Andrew Judson.

70
00:11:47,246 --> 00:11:51,087
Hi, Mr. Judson, this is uh,
Johnny-- John Petrie.

71
00:11:51,087 --> 00:11:53,454
Yes, yes, yes,
I've been waiting for you to call.

72
00:11:53,454 --> 00:11:55,470
Yeah, I think there's been
some kind of mistake.

73
00:11:55,470 --> 00:11:57,582
I don't know
any Benjamin Conroy.

74
00:11:57,582 --> 00:11:59,885
Uh, it's no mistake,
the estate of Mr. Conroy

75
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,413
has been willed to you
as of your 18th birthday,

76
00:12:02,413 --> 00:12:04,142
which was a few days ago,
if I'm correct.

77
00:12:04,142 --> 00:12:06,126
Yeah, but uh, again I--

78
00:12:06,126 --> 00:12:08,366
The property's worth
a substantial amount of money.

79
00:12:08,366 --> 00:12:11,053
I really need to go over
all the logistics in person.

80
00:12:11,053 --> 00:12:13,606
When's the soonest
you can come to Wellfield?

81
00:12:15,213 --> 00:12:17,293
See, that's the thing,
I can't exactly just leave.

82
00:12:18,285 --> 00:12:19,659
- Uh, Mr. Judson, I'll call you back.
- Yes, of course, but--

83
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:23,045
Hi, Mom.

84
00:12:24,621 --> 00:12:25,773
New doctor?

85
00:12:25,773 --> 00:12:27,661
I ran into Helen Sampson today

86
00:12:27,661 --> 00:12:30,125
and she told me about this new
medication her daughter was prescribed

87
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:32,172
for generalized anxiety
and mild depression.

88
00:12:32,172 --> 00:12:35,949
Dr. Webster said it was too dangerous
to take with my Klonopin and Valium.

89
00:12:35,949 --> 00:12:37,891
So, I went to Helen's doctor and--

90
00:12:39,213 --> 00:12:41,164
he was more than happy
to prescribe it.

91
00:12:41,164 --> 00:12:42,828
That's great.

92
00:12:42,828 --> 00:12:44,803
That's the last time I see
that Webster quack.

93
00:12:49,868 --> 00:12:51,788
Hey, Mom, can I talk to you
about something?

94
00:12:51,788 --> 00:12:54,381
If this is about going to college
again, you can stop right there.

95
00:12:54,381 --> 00:12:57,004
Those communal showers
are nothing but state sanctioned

96
00:12:57,004 --> 00:12:58,764
homosexual bath houses.

97
00:12:58,764 --> 00:13:01,388
No, I-- I was wondering
if I could go, uh--

98
00:13:01,388 --> 00:13:03,180
to church?

99
00:13:03,180 --> 00:13:06,124
Don't think I don't know how long
it's been since your last confession.

100
00:13:06,124 --> 00:13:09,035
No, Mom, to this town.

101
00:13:09,035 --> 00:13:10,923
It's called Wellfield.

102
00:13:10,923 --> 00:13:12,101
It's in Maine.

103
00:13:13,227 --> 00:13:14,283
Pardon me?

104
00:13:14,283 --> 00:13:15,948
I got this letter today and--

105
00:13:15,948 --> 00:13:18,059
You're not going anywhere,
do you you hear me?

106
00:13:18,059 --> 00:13:20,427
I am your mother and I make
the rules around here.

107
00:13:20,427 --> 00:13:21,867
So, not another word.

108
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:24,619
- But--
- Not another word.

109
00:13:24,619 --> 00:13:26,113
Who's Benjamin Conroy?

110
00:13:44,011 --> 00:13:45,931
- Are you Mary's son?
- Yes.

111
00:13:45,931 --> 00:13:47,498
I wanted to hold her
for a few days

112
00:13:47,498 --> 00:13:50,219
for a more thorough
psych evaluation.

113
00:13:50,219 --> 00:13:53,318
Which, trust me,
sounds much worse than it is.

114
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,522
- A few days?
- Yeah.

115
00:14:14,058 --> 00:14:15,305
Mr. Judson?

116
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,240
Hey, man?

117
00:15:07,144 --> 00:15:08,360
Hi.

118
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:10,024
You look a little lost.

119
00:15:10,024 --> 00:15:11,079
No, I'm fine.

120
00:15:11,079 --> 00:15:12,422
Sure about that?

121
00:15:14,568 --> 00:15:17,000
Kind of looking
for this lawyer's office.

122
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,176
Well, Mr. John Petrie,

123
00:15:19,176 --> 00:15:20,360
it's just around
the corner there.

124
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,448
Great, thank you.

125
00:15:21,448 --> 00:15:23,144
If you want my advice,
which you do,

126
00:15:23,144 --> 00:15:26,855
you'll turn around and get
your sorry ass back on that train.

127
00:15:26,855 --> 00:15:27,847
Why would I do that?

128
00:15:27,847 --> 00:15:28,903
Listen to him, okay?

129
00:15:28,903 --> 00:15:30,015
Nobody wants you here.

130
00:15:32,135 --> 00:15:34,919
Everything's been fine here
for 17 years.

131
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:37,288
You had no right coming back
and digging up the past!

132
00:15:37,288 --> 00:15:38,597
Listen, I don't know
what you're talking about.

133
00:15:42,055 --> 00:15:43,143
Hey.

134
00:15:43,143 --> 00:15:44,967
Let him go, Mack.

135
00:15:44,967 --> 00:15:48,744
Just so we're clear,
you don't belong in this town.

136
00:15:48,744 --> 00:15:50,020
Understand?

137
00:15:53,735 --> 00:15:54,912
See you around.

138
00:16:17,734 --> 00:16:21,605
So, I'm glad you were able
to come up here so quickly.

139
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:23,174
The sooner we get
the ball rolling,

140
00:16:23,174 --> 00:16:26,086
the sooner both of us can be
on our way to the bank.

141
00:16:26,086 --> 00:16:27,330
Uh-huh.

142
00:16:29,062 --> 00:16:30,556
Your mother was okay
with you coming up here?

143
00:16:33,254 --> 00:16:36,036
Well, it's not like she really has
any say in what I do.

144
00:16:40,197 --> 00:16:41,893
Mr. Judson, I've still got
a few questions.

145
00:16:41,893 --> 00:16:43,868
Ah, here we are.

146
00:16:58,245 --> 00:16:59,845
Just look at it.

147
00:16:59,845 --> 00:17:01,220
Okay.

148
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:04,196
You have the house over here,
barn out back.

149
00:17:04,196 --> 00:17:06,405
Property stretches
far into the woods over there

150
00:17:06,405 --> 00:17:09,307
covering approximately
125 acres.

151
00:17:10,117 --> 00:17:12,133
- Mr. Judson--
- I already have a developer lined up

152
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:14,052
who's been waiting years
to get a hold of the property.

153
00:17:14,052 --> 00:17:16,036
So, I was able to negotiate
a great price--

154
00:17:16,036 --> 00:17:17,149
pending your approval.

155
00:17:20,965 --> 00:17:23,140
Wait, can you just--
hold on a second.

156
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:24,740
Yeah, what is it?

157
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:26,500
Who is Benjamin Conroy?

158
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:29,412
I'm sorry, I just--
I just thought you knew.

159
00:17:29,412 --> 00:17:30,884
No.

160
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:32,516
You should really talk
to your mother about this.

161
00:17:32,516 --> 00:17:33,860
Trust me, it's not my place.

162
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,717
Look, I tried--
she wouldn't tell me.

163
00:17:35,717 --> 00:17:37,443
More reason for me
not to get involved.

164
00:17:37,443 --> 00:17:39,652
Please, I'm just trying
to figure out why I'm here.

165
00:17:41,955 --> 00:17:44,411
Because you're next of kin
to the Conroy family.

166
00:17:45,604 --> 00:17:47,043
Next of kin?

167
00:17:47,043 --> 00:17:49,148
Was Benjamin
like a c-c-c cousin or somethin'?

168
00:17:50,243 --> 00:17:52,739
No, not a cousin.

169
00:17:52,739 --> 00:17:54,016
Well, what then?

170
00:17:56,803 --> 00:17:59,364
Benjamin Conroy was--

171
00:17:59,364 --> 00:18:01,054
Benjamin Conroy was your father.

172
00:18:03,075 --> 00:18:04,931
See, I knew this had
to be a mistake.

173
00:18:04,931 --> 00:18:07,298
My father's name was Ed Petrie,
he died years ago.

174
00:18:07,298 --> 00:18:10,243
Your mother...
was Benjamin's sister.

175
00:18:10,243 --> 00:18:12,315
She adopted you after
your family passed away.

176
00:18:13,379 --> 00:18:15,299
That's impossible,
I'd remember something like that.

177
00:18:15,299 --> 00:18:16,673
You were only a year old.

178
00:18:21,218 --> 00:18:23,607
I'm sorry you had
to find out like this.

179
00:18:29,219 --> 00:18:30,402
Hey.

180
00:18:30,402 --> 00:18:31,810
I don't know how tame he is.

181
00:18:31,810 --> 00:18:32,834
Get outta here!

182
00:18:32,834 --> 00:18:36,418
Get, go, go,
get outta here, go, go!

183
00:18:36,418 --> 00:18:38,434
You okay,
he didn't hurt you?

184
00:18:38,434 --> 00:18:39,546
No, I'm fine.

185
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:44,192
Let's go see the house.

186
00:18:48,322 --> 00:18:49,566
All right.

187
00:18:52,930 --> 00:18:55,938
Had the power turned on
for showing the buyers.

188
00:18:55,938 --> 00:18:58,657
I also had an antiques dealer
put a quote together,

189
00:18:58,657 --> 00:19:00,833
assuming you want
to sell the furniture.

190
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:03,353
Minus a small percentage
for my finder's fee.

191
00:19:04,578 --> 00:19:06,039
Is this my family?

192
00:19:07,810 --> 00:19:09,631
Yes, I suppose so.

193
00:19:10,849 --> 00:19:11,929
What happened to them?

194
00:19:14,273 --> 00:19:15,457
Mr. Judson?

195
00:19:15,457 --> 00:19:18,336
Honestly, I really don't know
that much about it.

196
00:19:18,336 --> 00:19:19,798
Some kinda accident.

197
00:19:27,457 --> 00:19:30,816
I have a four o'clock,
so we need to get going.

198
00:19:30,816 --> 00:19:32,507
- Already?
- Yeah.

199
00:19:34,816 --> 00:19:38,016
So, the property was
originally made in 1816.

200
00:19:38,016 --> 00:19:40,001
Back then it sat on 400 acres.

201
00:19:40,001 --> 00:19:41,756
It was originally farm country.

202
00:19:48,736 --> 00:19:51,487
So, I booked you a room
at the hotel by my office.

203
00:19:51,487 --> 00:19:54,422
So, we can meet tomorrow morning
and go over all the paperwork.

204
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:00,672
Actually...I was kind of thinkin'
that I might like to stay here

205
00:20:00,672 --> 00:20:02,494
for a little longer.

206
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:04,831
Is that okay?

207
00:20:04,831 --> 00:20:06,080
I mean, it is your house,

208
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,096
but I wouldn't suggest
poking around in there.

209
00:20:08,096 --> 00:20:09,279
Why not?

210
00:20:09,279 --> 00:20:12,313
It's just...it's not sanitary.

211
00:20:14,079 --> 00:20:15,192
I'd like to stay.

212
00:20:16,415 --> 00:20:18,652
I mean, I'm staying.

213
00:20:19,775 --> 00:20:21,086
Fine.

214
00:20:21,086 --> 00:20:23,327
Okay, here's my card,

215
00:20:23,327 --> 00:20:25,790
the number for a cab service.

216
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:28,095
Give 'em a call
when you're done,

217
00:20:28,095 --> 00:20:30,517
assuming you haven't caught
some sort of hepatitis by then.

218
00:20:35,647 --> 00:20:36,831
Enjoy.

219
00:20:36,831 --> 00:20:38,325
- Thank you.
- I guess.

220
00:20:39,871 --> 00:20:43,166
Oh, and uh, Johnny...
happy birthday.

221
00:23:05,754 --> 00:23:07,063
Ow!

222
00:23:24,890 --> 00:23:26,166
Great.

223
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:54,649
Hello?

224
00:23:54,649 --> 00:23:56,569
Hi, John, it's Andrew Judson.

225
00:23:56,569 --> 00:23:58,552
I just called to let you know
I had the line turned back on.

226
00:23:58,552 --> 00:24:00,121
Oh, okay.

227
00:24:00,121 --> 00:24:01,528
Thanks, Mr. Judson.

228
00:24:01,528 --> 00:24:03,161
Is everything all right?

229
00:24:03,161 --> 00:24:04,728
Yeah, everything's fine.

230
00:24:04,728 --> 00:24:06,840
Okay, give me a call
if you need anything.

231
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:08,312
All right, I will.

232
00:24:08,312 --> 00:24:09,560
I'll see you tomorrow.

233
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:10,837
Sounds good, thank you.

234
00:24:19,193 --> 00:24:20,469
Hello?

235
00:25:22,038 --> 00:25:23,664
Bryan Conroy.

236
00:25:45,845 --> 00:25:46,991
Who's up there?

237
00:27:18,674 --> 00:27:19,689
Hey!

238
00:27:27,474 --> 00:27:28,620
Hello?

239
00:27:49,713 --> 00:27:51,698
Can I help you?

240
00:27:51,698 --> 00:27:53,389
I'm sorry I scared you.

241
00:27:54,865 --> 00:27:56,626
I didn't think anyone
would be coming back,

242
00:27:56,626 --> 00:27:58,152
so I kinda panicked.

243
00:27:59,186 --> 00:28:00,306
Okay.

244
00:28:00,306 --> 00:28:02,673
Though technically, I think
you're the one who barged in on me,

245
00:28:02,673 --> 00:28:04,817
so I don't think I should be
the one apologizing.

246
00:28:04,817 --> 00:28:06,385
Why, I didn't barge in, I--

247
00:28:06,385 --> 00:28:08,081
You didn't exactly knock either,
did you?

248
00:28:08,081 --> 00:28:09,361
No, I didn't knock--

249
00:28:09,361 --> 00:28:11,946
Well, now that we've established that,
I'll be upstairs.

250
00:28:13,297 --> 00:28:14,738
Hey!

251
00:28:14,738 --> 00:28:16,114
Uh, who are you?

252
00:28:16,114 --> 00:28:18,704
See, I should be asking you
the same question.

253
00:28:18,704 --> 00:28:21,553
- Yeah, but this is my house.
- And?

254
00:28:21,553 --> 00:28:23,346
Not looking for a roommate?

255
00:28:23,346 --> 00:28:26,032
Not exactly, I'm supposed
to be selling it tomorrow.

256
00:28:26,032 --> 00:28:28,177
If I wasn't mistaken,
that would be your way

257
00:28:28,177 --> 00:28:30,097
of telling me I had to leave.

258
00:28:30,097 --> 00:28:32,113
Kind of-- sorry.

259
00:28:32,113 --> 00:28:33,193
No worries.

260
00:28:34,705 --> 00:28:35,784
Whatever.

261
00:28:37,265 --> 00:28:39,272
- No, wait, slow down.
- No, thanks.

262
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,255
Do you have a name?

263
00:28:42,192 --> 00:28:43,824
I'm not a stray cat.

264
00:28:43,824 --> 00:28:45,936
Of course I have a name.

265
00:28:45,936 --> 00:28:47,920
Well, what is it?

266
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:51,025
- Emma.
- Emma, I'm Johnny.

267
00:28:51,025 --> 00:28:52,145
I'm sure you are.

268
00:28:52,145 --> 00:28:53,457
So, you've been living here?

269
00:28:53,457 --> 00:28:55,377
- You can say that.
- Why?

270
00:28:55,377 --> 00:28:58,576
It's been abandoned for years,
I didn't think anyone would mind.

271
00:28:58,576 --> 00:29:00,176
What, did you run away
or something?

272
00:29:00,176 --> 00:29:01,584
Something.

273
00:29:01,584 --> 00:29:02,631
Do you have anywhere to go?

274
00:29:03,791 --> 00:29:04,970
All right, enough.

275
00:29:05,264 --> 00:29:07,600
- What?
- With the questions, okay?

276
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:09,839
I'm sorry, I didn't expect
anybody to be here.

277
00:29:09,839 --> 00:29:13,199
Well, I'm leaving, so you can go ahead
and pretend like it never happened.

278
00:29:13,199 --> 00:29:14,093
Emma.

279
00:29:15,343 --> 00:29:16,270
What?

280
00:29:18,383 --> 00:29:21,199
Would you mind showing me
around the place before you take off?

281
00:29:21,199 --> 00:29:23,053
I think you can handle it yourself.

282
00:29:23,823 --> 00:29:25,038
Please?

283
00:29:25,038 --> 00:29:26,315
I'd really appreciate it.

284
00:29:27,504 --> 00:29:29,226
I suppose.

285
00:29:30,479 --> 00:29:32,143
Guess we'll start
with the basement.

286
00:29:32,143 --> 00:29:33,899
I saw some bulbs
down there a while back.

287
00:29:37,903 --> 00:29:39,438
So, how long have you been here?

288
00:29:39,438 --> 00:29:40,654
I don't know, a day or two.

289
00:29:40,654 --> 00:29:42,094
Watch your step.

290
00:29:42,094 --> 00:29:45,193
I didn't think I'd witness the return
of the prodigal son, though.

291
00:29:46,062 --> 00:29:47,823
What are you talking about?

292
00:29:47,823 --> 00:29:49,677
You're the long lost Conroy, right?

293
00:29:50,958 --> 00:29:52,168
Wait, you know who I am?

294
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:56,559
The whole town knows
who you are.

295
00:29:56,559 --> 00:29:58,350
Or at least they think they do.

296
00:29:58,350 --> 00:30:00,292
Why do they know about me?

297
00:30:03,437 --> 00:30:04,866
Again with the questions.

298
00:30:19,598 --> 00:30:20,940
Hey, Johnny.

299
00:30:31,853 --> 00:30:33,740
- Sorry.
- Relax.

300
00:30:36,397 --> 00:30:38,477
I was probably gonna be here
for a few more hours,

301
00:30:38,477 --> 00:30:39,916
if you wanted to stick around.

302
00:30:39,916 --> 00:30:41,029
I don't know.

303
00:30:42,092 --> 00:30:44,012
To be honest,
I could use the company.

304
00:30:44,012 --> 00:30:45,606
I don't really know anybody
around here.

305
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:49,286
Guess I don't have
anything else to do.

306
00:30:53,996 --> 00:30:56,069
Don't tell me there's somebody else
staying here too.

307
00:30:56,716 --> 00:30:57,764
No.

308
00:31:45,067 --> 00:31:46,376
Is there anybody up here?

309
00:32:09,258 --> 00:32:10,794
The upstairs is empty.

310
00:32:10,794 --> 00:32:12,554
Looks like the door blew open.

311
00:32:12,554 --> 00:32:14,314
Oh.

312
00:32:14,314 --> 00:32:18,536
Johnny...
do you believe in ghosts?

313
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:23,593
You should see
your face right now.

314
00:32:23,593 --> 00:32:25,088
Ohh.

315
00:32:47,113 --> 00:32:48,226
Emma.

316
00:33:06,344 --> 00:33:07,784
Hey.

317
00:33:07,784 --> 00:33:09,353
You can smoke in the house
if you want to.

318
00:33:09,353 --> 00:33:11,840
- I don't care.
- Shut up, I don't smoke.

319
00:33:13,512 --> 00:33:14,625
Give me a push.

320
00:33:23,336 --> 00:33:25,065
Have you been in the barn?

321
00:33:25,065 --> 00:33:27,272
Gross, no.

322
00:33:27,272 --> 00:33:29,345
Just looking at it gives me tetanus.

323
00:33:32,712 --> 00:33:34,686
So, what are you going to do
when you sell this place?

324
00:33:36,104 --> 00:33:39,144
Probably head back to the city,
finish school.

325
00:33:39,144 --> 00:33:40,647
Maybe use the money
to go to college.

326
00:33:40,647 --> 00:33:42,023
You're from New York?

327
00:33:42,023 --> 00:33:43,816
Yeah, born and raised.

328
00:33:43,816 --> 00:33:46,311
Well, raised.

329
00:33:46,311 --> 00:33:47,358
Don't you love it?

330
00:33:48,327 --> 00:33:50,088
You know, I honestly
never got out much,

331
00:33:50,088 --> 00:33:52,104
aside seeing
in school and church.

332
00:33:52,104 --> 00:33:54,308
Jesus, why the hell
do you want to go back?

333
00:33:56,136 --> 00:33:57,346
I don't know.

334
00:33:57,831 --> 00:34:00,700
Guess I always thought
I'd eventually have to.

335
00:34:01,127 --> 00:34:04,094
If I were you, I'd just pick up
and start over.

336
00:34:05,447 --> 00:34:08,936
New town, new place,
new name.

337
00:34:08,936 --> 00:34:10,244
New everything.

338
00:34:11,622 --> 00:34:13,607
Is that what you did?

339
00:34:13,607 --> 00:34:14,686
Come on.

340
00:34:17,190 --> 00:34:19,014
Where?

341
00:34:19,014 --> 00:34:20,869
You said you wanted
to see the barn, right?

342
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:27,259
It's locked from the inside.

343
00:34:29,574 --> 00:34:30,784
I think I can get in
from the top.

344
00:34:42,662 --> 00:34:44,484
- You comin'?
- Absolutely not.

345
00:34:51,621 --> 00:34:52,701
Caw!

346
00:34:54,373 --> 00:34:55,617
Johnnie?

347
00:34:56,006 --> 00:34:57,052
Yeah.

348
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:12,636
You gotta see this!

349
00:36:38,979 --> 00:36:40,288
Johnny?

350
00:36:41,251 --> 00:36:42,363
Coming.

351
00:36:54,721 --> 00:36:55,649
What's wrong?

352
00:36:56,641 --> 00:36:57,656
I don't know.

353
00:36:58,657 --> 00:37:00,642
There was someone
behind me.

354
00:37:00,642 --> 00:37:01,689
Who?

355
00:37:04,129 --> 00:37:05,602
Anything upstairs?

356
00:37:05,602 --> 00:37:07,292
No, jus-- just junk.

357
00:37:14,977 --> 00:37:17,213
- We should probably go inside.
- Yeah.

358
00:37:26,848 --> 00:37:28,125
Go on, get away!

359
00:37:30,977 --> 00:37:32,089
Get away!

360
00:37:42,528 --> 00:37:43,772
You owe me one.

361
00:38:09,024 --> 00:38:12,256
Don't step another foot
in this room, you pervert!

362
00:38:12,256 --> 00:38:15,671
Michael Coffit, please call 8-4-0.

363
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:23,743
You've reached the Petrie's.

364
00:38:23,743 --> 00:38:25,855
Please leave your name
and a brief message

365
00:38:25,855 --> 00:38:28,383
and have a blessed day.

366
00:38:28,383 --> 00:38:30,975
Johnny, this is your mother again.

367
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:32,863
I don't know what kind
of joke you're playing,

368
00:38:32,863 --> 00:38:34,463
but I expect you here first thing
in the morning

369
00:38:34,463 --> 00:38:35,837
to get me out of this place!

370
00:38:44,510 --> 00:38:47,615
So, do you know anything
about my family?

371
00:38:47,615 --> 00:38:48,927
That depends.

372
00:38:48,927 --> 00:38:50,334
What do you already know?

373
00:38:50,334 --> 00:38:51,676
That there was an accident.

374
00:38:52,223 --> 00:38:54,526
I wouldn't exactly say that.

375
00:38:54,526 --> 00:38:56,255
Well, what happened then?

376
00:38:56,255 --> 00:38:58,294
How should I know,
it's your family not mine.

377
00:38:59,646 --> 00:39:00,766
I don't know.

378
00:39:00,766 --> 00:39:03,995
I just felt connected to this place
from the second I got here.

379
00:39:06,014 --> 00:39:09,182
There is this strong,
tragic energy, right?

380
00:39:09,182 --> 00:39:11,454
Just looking at the photos
you can tell.

381
00:39:11,454 --> 00:39:13,723
At one point the Conroys
were happy.

382
00:39:17,662 --> 00:39:20,158
Listen, it's getting pretty late.

383
00:39:20,158 --> 00:39:21,534
I get it, time to go.

384
00:39:21,534 --> 00:39:25,277
No, wait, I was gonna say
I'm spending the night, so...

385
00:39:25,277 --> 00:39:26,936
if you wanted to stay another day.

386
00:39:27,773 --> 00:39:29,117
Thanks.

387
00:39:29,117 --> 00:39:30,366
You're welcome.

388
00:39:30,366 --> 00:39:31,517
What's wrong?

389
00:39:31,517 --> 00:39:34,781
You know how I said I-- I thought I saw
someone outside earlier?

390
00:39:34,781 --> 00:39:36,155
I think they're back.

391
00:39:41,021 --> 00:39:42,712
- Did you hear that?
- Sh-hh.

392
00:40:31,452 --> 00:40:34,940
Go ahead, Mack, let 'em know
who's house this is!

393
00:40:36,315 --> 00:40:38,363
Why don't you come out,
Mr. John Petrie?

394
00:40:38,363 --> 00:40:39,963
We ain't gonna hurt you!

395
00:40:39,963 --> 00:40:41,756
What, you gotta be kidding me.

396
00:40:41,756 --> 00:40:43,097
Wait, what are you gonna do?

397
00:40:43,964 --> 00:40:45,109
I'm calling the cops.

398
00:40:47,483 --> 00:40:49,340
Open up, buddy!

399
00:40:49,340 --> 00:40:50,556
We just wanna hang out!

400
00:40:50,556 --> 00:40:52,859
There are people trying
to break into my house.

401
00:40:52,859 --> 00:40:54,458
No, I'm not sure
of the address exactly.

402
00:40:54,458 --> 00:40:55,610
It's-- it's the Conroy farm.

403
00:40:56,603 --> 00:40:58,171
There's things you need to know.

404
00:40:58,171 --> 00:40:59,674
So, let us in this house.

405
00:40:59,674 --> 00:41:01,714
I just need you guys to send
somebody right away, please.

406
00:41:15,963 --> 00:41:17,108
What are you looking at?

407
00:41:18,842 --> 00:41:19,922
Mack?

408
00:41:22,810 --> 00:41:24,538
It's for the good of us all.

409
00:41:24,538 --> 00:41:25,529
What?

410
00:41:25,529 --> 00:41:26,810
Thank you.

411
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:28,271
Okay, they should be here soon.

412
00:41:30,650 --> 00:41:31,827
Emma?

413
00:41:35,482 --> 00:41:36,857
Where'd you go?

414
00:41:39,289 --> 00:41:40,784
Oh, fuck.

415
00:41:42,778 --> 00:41:44,687
Mack, we gotta bail.

416
00:41:45,913 --> 00:41:47,161
What, why?

417
00:41:47,161 --> 00:41:48,282
There's someone out back.

418
00:41:48,282 --> 00:41:49,492
Yo, Mack, let's go, come on.

419
00:41:54,937 --> 00:41:56,311
Emma, is that you?

420
00:42:27,032 --> 00:42:28,952
You shouldn't a come back here.

421
00:42:28,952 --> 00:42:31,570
You let them out, you know that,
you let them out!

422
00:42:35,736 --> 00:42:38,070
All right, Henry, let's go,
come on, it's gettin' late.

423
00:42:42,167 --> 00:42:43,476
No, no.

424
00:42:44,888 --> 00:42:46,066
Watch your step.

425
00:42:47,032 --> 00:42:48,592
There you go.

426
00:42:50,359 --> 00:42:51,733
Nice and easy now, okay?

427
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,911
We're just gonna
take him down to the station

428
00:42:53,911 --> 00:42:55,668
and throw him
in the drunk tank for the night.

429
00:42:55,991 --> 00:42:57,650
Who-- who is he?

430
00:42:58,391 --> 00:43:00,725
Henry Depford,
he used to be a sheriff up here.

431
00:43:01,431 --> 00:43:03,406
Honestly, he's a pretty harmless guy.

432
00:43:04,854 --> 00:43:06,200
You might want to tell him that.

433
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:08,599
I think he wasjust trying
to scare you, is all.

434
00:43:08,599 --> 00:43:11,730
Well, Henry became pretty
obsessed with this place,

435
00:43:11,927 --> 00:43:14,007
uh, after he discovered
the bodies in the barn.

436
00:43:14,007 --> 00:43:15,414
He found the bodies?

437
00:43:15,414 --> 00:43:17,654
Yeah, Bryan, he's the one who found you
hidden in the basement that night.

438
00:43:17,654 --> 00:43:18,774
I'm sorry, what did you call me?

439
00:43:18,774 --> 00:43:19,723
You're name's Bryan, right?

440
00:43:20,855 --> 00:43:22,797
Yeah, right, I'm sorry, I'm just, um--

441
00:43:23,895 --> 00:43:24,887
a little on edge.

442
00:43:24,887 --> 00:43:26,071
I can understand that.

443
00:43:26,071 --> 00:43:27,085
You stayin' up here by yourself?

444
00:43:29,174 --> 00:43:31,030
Uh, yeah, just for tonight.

445
00:43:31,030 --> 00:43:32,119
Right, right.

446
00:43:32,119 --> 00:43:34,870
Well, you want to press charges,
you come down to the station tomorrow--

447
00:43:34,870 --> 00:43:35,894
No, no, it's okay.

448
00:43:35,894 --> 00:43:37,654
Uh, can you just make sure
that he doesn't come back?

449
00:43:37,654 --> 00:43:38,710
I'll have a talk with him.

450
00:43:38,710 --> 00:43:40,277
- Thank you.
- All right?

451
00:43:40,277 --> 00:43:41,587
Be careful up here, all right?

452
00:44:00,245 --> 00:44:01,739
Eventful evening.

453
00:44:05,430 --> 00:44:08,053
Hey, why did you disappear?

454
00:44:08,053 --> 00:44:09,718
Wow, what?

455
00:44:09,718 --> 00:44:11,026
Been here the whole time.

456
00:44:11,477 --> 00:44:12,854
No you haven't.

457
00:44:12,854 --> 00:44:14,992
You're right, fine, I lied.

458
00:44:16,117 --> 00:44:17,742
Yeah, you do that a lot,
don't you?

459
00:44:22,805 --> 00:44:24,629
I like you, Johnny.

460
00:44:24,629 --> 00:44:25,839
But you'll never know me.

461
00:44:27,669 --> 00:44:29,555
That doesn't mean
we can't be friends.

462
00:45:08,788 --> 00:45:10,484
Johnny?

463
00:45:10,484 --> 00:45:12,371
- Hi, Mom.
- Where the hell have you been?

464
00:45:12,371 --> 00:45:14,996
I've been trying to get
a hold of you all day.

465
00:45:14,996 --> 00:45:16,243
I'm home, Mom.

466
00:45:16,243 --> 00:45:19,113
Well, get back here immediately
and bring me my prescriptions.

467
00:45:19,411 --> 00:45:21,036
No, I mean I'm in my home--

468
00:45:21,683 --> 00:45:23,731
in Wellfield.

469
00:45:23,731 --> 00:45:26,516
I can't believe you deliberately
disobeyed me like this.

470
00:45:26,516 --> 00:45:28,051
You better get back here, Johnny!

471
00:45:28,051 --> 00:45:30,066
No, I can't believe you didn't tell me.

472
00:45:30,066 --> 00:45:32,270
How could you hide the truth
from me about my family?

473
00:45:34,930 --> 00:45:36,109
Mom?

474
00:45:37,746 --> 00:45:39,240
You don't understand, Johnny.

475
00:45:42,002 --> 00:45:43,731
Benjamin was an awful man.

476
00:45:43,731 --> 00:45:45,522
I couldn't let you
grow up like that.

477
00:45:45,522 --> 00:45:46,803
So, you lied to me instead?

478
00:45:46,803 --> 00:45:48,083
I didn't lie to you, I just--

479
00:45:48,083 --> 00:45:49,682
just left out the truth?

480
00:45:49,682 --> 00:45:52,048
Just come back here
and we'll discuss this.

481
00:45:53,874 --> 00:45:55,303
I don't know if I'm coming back.

482
00:45:57,650 --> 00:45:59,340
Johnny, please don't do this.

483
00:47:12,912 --> 00:47:14,438
Stupid.

484
00:47:52,687 --> 00:47:54,629
I'm sorry, did I say
you could come in?

485
00:47:57,519 --> 00:47:58,860
Johnny.

486
00:48:00,142 --> 00:48:01,670
That feels good.

487
00:48:27,917 --> 00:48:29,511
Sorry, Bryan.

488
00:49:31,404 --> 00:49:33,095
Save my dying soul.

489
00:49:46,187 --> 00:49:47,755
What's wrong?

490
00:49:47,755 --> 00:49:49,511
You saw something out there,
didn't you?

491
00:49:53,195 --> 00:49:54,307
Yeah.

492
00:50:02,027 --> 00:50:04,777
I didn't hear someone,
just a creak before you got here.

493
00:50:06,538 --> 00:50:08,065
You woke something up.

494
00:50:09,259 --> 00:50:10,858
It's my family.

495
00:50:10,858 --> 00:50:12,288
I think they need my help.

496
00:50:13,354 --> 00:50:15,115
Something touched me
in the other room

497
00:50:15,115 --> 00:50:17,835
and it definitely wasn't
asking for help.

498
00:50:17,835 --> 00:50:19,466
Look, I get if you want to leave.

499
00:50:19,466 --> 00:50:22,184
But I'm not going anywhere
until I find out what happened to them.

500
00:50:22,698 --> 00:50:24,226
I never said I was leaving.

501
00:50:48,425 --> 00:50:50,530
You son of a bitch.

502
