00:55:07,554 --> 00:55:08,536
Emma?

529
00:55:11,746 --> 00:55:13,240
Emma, is that you?

530
00:55:18,658 --> 00:55:20,218
Emma, what the hell
are you doing?

531
00:55:50,049 --> 00:55:51,259
Are you sure about this?

532
00:56:05,344 --> 00:56:06,905
Missed you, brother.

533
00:56:10,432 --> 00:56:11,479
Emma?

534
00:56:12,352 --> 00:56:13,661
What just happened?

535
00:57:41,726 --> 00:57:44,060
You don't actually believe
any of this stuff, do you?

536
00:57:45,725 --> 00:57:46,813
I don't know.

537
00:57:46,813 --> 00:57:49,147
It-- it might have something to do
with what happened to my family.

538
00:58:15,772 --> 00:58:17,404
Oh!

539
00:58:17,404 --> 00:58:19,260
Johnny, what's wrong?

540
00:58:25,371 --> 00:58:26,746
Grab the other side.

541
00:58:45,148 --> 00:58:46,424
You okay?

542
00:58:52,092 --> 00:58:54,972
I evoke thee,
oh God of Osiris

543
00:58:54,972 --> 00:58:58,681
in the virtue of the most holy
sacrament, Jesus Christ.

544
00:58:59,099 --> 00:59:04,379
Who, for our redemption,
was crucified, suffered death,

545
00:59:04,379 --> 00:59:07,098
was buried, and rose on the 3rd day

546
00:59:07,098 --> 00:59:10,414
by the power of the spirit
of the God Osiris.

547
00:59:11,867 --> 00:59:13,339
We pray to thee, oh Lords.

548
00:59:13,339 --> 00:59:14,418
Amen.

549
00:59:15,419 --> 00:59:16,730
Amen.

550
00:59:16,730 --> 00:59:17,778
Amen.

551
00:59:34,810 --> 00:59:37,882
I, Benjamin,

552
00:59:37,882 --> 00:59:41,013
share the gift of the afterlife

553
00:59:41,626 --> 00:59:43,130
with Bryan.

554
00:59:57,497 --> 00:59:59,866
I, Elizabeth,

555
00:59:59,866 --> 01:00:02,254
share the gift of the afterlife
with Bryan.

556
01:00:09,337 --> 01:00:11,065
I, Faith,

557
01:00:11,065 --> 01:00:14,131
share the gift of the afterlife
with Bryan.

558
01:00:40,248 --> 01:00:41,175
Daniel?

559
01:00:43,704 --> 01:00:46,136
- Say it, Daniel.
-Johnny!

560
01:00:46,136 --> 01:00:48,111
Johnny!
What happened?

561
01:00:48,888 --> 01:00:52,088
It was-- they were--
they were all right here, all of them.

562
01:00:52,088 --> 01:00:53,528
- Calm down, okay?
- No.

563
01:00:53,528 --> 01:00:54,840
There's no one here but us.

564
01:00:54,840 --> 01:00:56,343
Just you and me.

565
01:00:56,343 --> 01:00:57,976
It was right in front of me,
I could feel it.

566
01:00:57,976 --> 01:00:59,704
I could feel his breath
on my face.

567
01:00:59,704 --> 01:01:03,288
Just you and me, hear me?

568
01:02:04,886 --> 01:02:06,102
What is it?

569
01:02:06,102 --> 01:02:07,084
Do you hearthat?

570
01:02:22,293 --> 01:02:24,405
- Mr. Judson.
- Are you okay?

571
01:02:24,405 --> 01:02:26,614
Yeah, I'm fine.

572
01:02:26,614 --> 01:02:27,797
I called the hotel this morning.

573
01:02:27,797 --> 01:02:29,045
They said you never
even checked in.

574
01:02:29,045 --> 01:02:32,886
You-- you know, I lost track of time
and I decided to crash here.

575
01:02:32,886 --> 01:02:34,827
Well, it would have been helpful
if you'd called to let me know.

576
01:02:36,532 --> 01:02:37,557
You're right, I'm sorry.

577
01:02:37,557 --> 01:02:38,677
I should have.

578
01:02:38,677 --> 01:02:41,013
All right, well,
we're both here now.

579
01:02:41,013 --> 01:02:42,835
What do you say
we get down to business?

580
01:02:44,340 --> 01:02:46,675
Um, sure.
Come on in.

581
01:02:59,156 --> 01:03:00,204
Hold on, hold on.

582
01:03:15,892 --> 01:03:18,292
The offer's well above
market value.

583
01:03:18,292 --> 01:03:20,595
So, probably, if I were you,

584
01:03:20,595 --> 01:03:22,734
I wouldn't even
bother negotiating.

585
01:03:24,724 --> 01:03:26,993
Just sign it,
be done with this dump.

586
01:03:28,531 --> 01:03:30,739
Yeah, I mean,
I'm sure it's great.

587
01:03:30,739 --> 01:03:33,139
Trust me, if you're holding out
for something better to come along,

588
01:03:33,139 --> 01:03:35,858
it will not be happening
in this economy.

589
01:03:35,858 --> 01:03:38,770
I trust you,
it's just I'm not really sure.

590
01:03:38,770 --> 01:03:42,035
I know, real estate can seem
like a daunting task sometimes.

591
01:03:42,035 --> 01:03:44,752
But that's why I'm here,
walk you through it.

592
01:03:48,498 --> 01:03:50,483
What if I didn't want
to sell the house?

593
01:03:50,483 --> 01:03:51,730
Excuse me?

594
01:03:51,730 --> 01:03:54,771
I just-- I sort of feel obligated
to keep it.

595
01:03:54,771 --> 01:03:56,274
It's my family's home.

596
01:03:56,274 --> 01:03:58,130
Johnny, you didn't even
know them.

597
01:03:58,130 --> 01:03:59,571
Yeah, I know that.

598
01:03:59,571 --> 01:04:02,482
Listen, kid, I took on this case
under the agreement

599
01:04:02,482 --> 01:04:03,911
that I receive a percentage
of the sale.

600
01:04:05,522 --> 01:04:06,834
I'm sorry, Mr. Judson.

601
01:04:06,834 --> 01:04:09,452
Then maybe you should rethink
making such a detrimental decision.

602
01:04:16,850 --> 01:04:18,890
This is the last thing
that I need.

603
01:04:20,402 --> 01:04:21,650
Who is that?

604
01:04:21,650 --> 01:04:22,961
He's been harassing me.

605
01:04:22,961 --> 01:04:24,690
That's David Mackey.

606
01:04:24,690 --> 01:04:26,033
Mack.

607
01:04:26,033 --> 01:04:29,969
Guess you could say he's your, uh...
half brother.

608
01:04:29,969 --> 01:04:30,918
What?

609
01:04:31,794 --> 01:04:35,569
Benjamin wasn't exactly the most...
faithful husband.

610
01:04:35,569 --> 01:04:37,361
But don't worry, he doesn't have
any claim to the estate.

611
01:04:37,361 --> 01:04:38,506
I'll handle it.

612
01:04:41,649 --> 01:04:42,827
My brother?

613
01:04:43,601 --> 01:04:45,650
Hey, David.

614
01:04:45,650 --> 01:04:47,761
Yeah, this really isn't the time
or the place--

615
01:04:47,761 --> 01:04:48,753
I just want to talk to him.

616
01:04:48,753 --> 01:04:51,313
Yeah, from what I understand
you already talked to him yesterday.

617
01:04:51,313 --> 01:04:52,433
I want to talk to Bryan.

618
01:04:52,433 --> 01:04:54,768
Uh, yeah, he goes by Johnny now.

619
01:04:54,768 --> 01:04:56,017
I want to talk to Bryan.

620
01:04:56,017 --> 01:04:57,162
Where'd Daniel put him?

621
01:05:00,049 --> 01:05:02,416
We can arrange a time,
a place, that's fine.

622
01:05:02,416 --> 01:05:04,208
Give me the baby, Daniel.

623
01:05:04,208 --> 01:05:05,361
Excuse me?

624
01:05:06,640 --> 01:05:08,560
No, there's one more.

625
01:05:08,560 --> 01:05:11,760
David, you really need
to get going now.

626
01:05:11,760 --> 01:05:13,320
- Hi.
- Hey.

627
01:05:15,088 --> 01:05:16,592
What's going on?

628
01:05:16,592 --> 01:05:17,770
I'm not sure.

629
01:05:18,961 --> 01:05:21,200
Give me the baby, Daniel!

630
01:05:21,200 --> 01:05:22,959
Bullshit!

631
01:05:22,959 --> 01:05:24,048
Oh, my God.

632
01:05:24,048 --> 01:05:25,200
David.

633
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:26,607
It has to be finished.

634
01:05:35,567 --> 01:05:36,975
Jesus!

635
01:05:47,696 --> 01:05:49,005
Bryan!

636
01:06:09,359 --> 01:06:10,504
Behind the door.

637
01:06:16,270 --> 01:06:17,382
Emma!

638
01:06:20,174 --> 01:06:23,279
Hey, just-- just let her go.

639
01:06:23,279 --> 01:06:24,805
I don't want her.

640
01:06:26,606 --> 01:06:27,915
There's one more.

641
01:06:53,357 --> 01:06:55,277
Help me, please!

642
01:06:55,277 --> 01:06:56,813
I'm sorry!

643
01:06:56,813 --> 01:06:58,733
Save our souls, Bryan!

644
01:06:58,733 --> 01:07:00,643
Ah!

645
01:07:12,492 --> 01:07:14,157
Hey, are you okay?

646
01:07:14,157 --> 01:07:15,532
Yeah, are you okay?

647
01:07:16,909 --> 01:07:18,476
He's dead.

648
01:07:18,476 --> 01:07:19,757
We gotta call the cops.

649
01:07:19,757 --> 01:07:20,909
You can't.

650
01:07:20,909 --> 01:07:22,285
We have to.

651
01:07:22,285 --> 01:07:23,430
No, Johnny, you can't.

652
01:07:26,892 --> 01:07:28,557
Judson had a--
had a cell phone.

653
01:07:28,557 --> 01:07:29,767
I'll go get it.

654
01:07:43,723 --> 01:07:45,228
He was right there.

655
01:07:45,228 --> 01:07:47,432
Come on, Johnny,
let's go inside.

656
01:07:50,764 --> 01:07:51,690
Hey!

657
01:07:52,811 --> 01:07:53,964
What are you doing back?

658
01:07:53,964 --> 01:07:56,428
What the hell did you do
with the bodies out there?

659
01:07:56,428 --> 01:07:57,802
I didn't touch the bodies.

660
01:08:07,403 --> 01:08:08,908
What's going on?

661
01:08:08,908 --> 01:08:10,603
Look, I've been
investigating this case

662
01:08:10,603 --> 01:08:12,969
since even after they forced me
into retirement.

663
01:08:14,507 --> 01:08:16,170
So, you know what happened?

664
01:08:16,170 --> 01:08:18,572
Yeah, I was there.

665
01:08:18,572 --> 01:08:21,195
Your father was convinced
that there was a code in the Bible

666
01:08:21,195 --> 01:08:24,043
that-- that somehow linked
the resurrection of Jesus

667
01:08:24,043 --> 01:08:26,091
to the Egyptian God Osiris--

668
01:08:26,091 --> 01:08:28,164
that he used it to rise
from the dead.

669
01:08:29,066 --> 01:08:30,922
I found his Bible last night.

670
01:08:30,922 --> 01:08:32,682
Well, there was only one problem.

671
01:08:32,682 --> 01:08:34,282
They never completed the ritual.

672
01:08:34,282 --> 01:08:37,930
And so your family
is now trapped in limbo.

673
01:08:37,930 --> 01:08:39,140
Wait!

674
01:08:40,010 --> 01:08:41,162
Why?

675
01:08:41,162 --> 01:08:42,634
They want the last survivor.

676
01:08:42,634 --> 01:08:44,074
Look, trust me.

677
01:08:44,074 --> 01:08:46,090
Until they have finished
what they've started,

678
01:08:46,090 --> 01:08:47,722
their souls can't move on.

679
01:08:47,722 --> 01:08:49,866
Your father told me
there was one more.

680
01:08:49,866 --> 01:08:52,553
One more?
That's what Mack said.

681
01:08:52,553 --> 01:08:54,569
Right now, they're out
looking for hosts.

682
01:08:54,569 --> 01:08:57,130
Now, the living,
they're very hard to control.

683
01:08:57,130 --> 01:08:59,136
But the dead,
free for the taking.

684
01:09:00,106 --> 01:09:01,354
What can I do to help?

685
01:09:01,354 --> 01:09:04,393
Years ago,
your brother Daniel saved your life

686
01:09:04,393 --> 01:09:06,089
by hiding you in the basement.

687
01:09:06,089 --> 01:09:09,351
And maybe if we contact him,
he'll do it again.

688
01:09:40,201 --> 01:09:41,477
Something's happening.

689
01:09:42,345 --> 01:09:43,360
What?

690
01:09:45,353 --> 01:09:47,589
Oh, we better hurry.

691
01:10:26,662 --> 01:10:28,572
We need
the quality of the sitters.

692
01:10:30,823 --> 01:10:32,416
Something that belongs to us.

693
01:11:03,910 --> 01:11:05,316
And the purpose.

694
01:11:14,278 --> 01:11:15,390
Now what?

695
01:11:16,485 --> 01:11:20,742
The dead sometimes send a marker
to connect them to the living.

696
01:11:20,742 --> 01:11:22,596
Um, a gift.

697
01:11:23,461 --> 01:11:25,795
Did you receive
anything like that?

698
01:11:45,861 --> 01:11:49,505
Well, we couldn't have picked
a better location.

699
01:11:53,444 --> 01:11:55,778
Well, do we hold hands now
or something?

700
01:11:58,405 --> 01:12:03,041
No, uh...
wejust wait.

701
01:12:09,508 --> 01:12:11,134
Daniel, are you there?

702
01:12:22,435 --> 01:12:23,580
Daniel?

703
01:12:24,804 --> 01:12:28,068
Daniel, it's me, Bryan.

704
01:12:34,083 --> 01:12:35,774
Daniel, we want to help you.

705
01:12:39,139 --> 01:12:40,153
He's here.

706
01:12:40,675 --> 01:12:42,649
Daniel, show us
how we can help you.

707
01:13:04,802 --> 01:13:06,012
Daniel, please.

708
01:13:25,026 --> 01:13:26,432
Fifth what?

709
01:13:47,393 --> 01:13:49,666
Fifth nail, what does that mean?

710
01:13:49,666 --> 01:13:51,136
I've heard about it before--

711
01:13:51,136 --> 01:13:53,441
in school-- it-- it--
it's supposed to go in the heart

712
01:13:53,441 --> 01:13:55,713
during a crucifixion
to end suffering.

713
01:13:55,713 --> 01:13:57,153
It was withheld from Jesus.

714
01:13:57,153 --> 01:14:00,501
They Conroys only had...
four nails each.

715
01:14:01,985 --> 01:14:03,840
There's one more.

716
01:14:05,792 --> 01:14:08,320
It wasn't you, it was the nail.

717
01:14:08,320 --> 01:14:09,953
Then why are they
still after me?

718
01:14:09,953 --> 01:14:12,033
Benjamin Conroy

719
01:14:12,033 --> 01:14:15,232
pledged the entire family
to Osiris.

720
01:14:15,232 --> 01:14:17,312
He has to fulfill his promise.

721
01:14:17,312 --> 01:14:18,970
But before he died,

722
01:14:19,777 --> 01:14:22,080
he didn't want
to finish the ritual.

723
01:14:22,080 --> 01:14:24,000
He wanted to end it.

724
01:14:25,920 --> 01:14:27,905
Oh, God,

725
01:14:27,905 --> 01:14:29,184
it worked.

726
01:14:29,184 --> 01:14:30,874
- Don't open it.
- It's my mother.

727
01:14:31,744 --> 01:14:34,400
- Come on.
- Hey, no, no, it's okay.

728
01:14:34,400 --> 01:14:37,279
- What are you doing here?
- I needed to see my baby.

729
01:14:37,279 --> 01:14:39,551
I'm so sorry for everything,
I shouldn't have come.

730
01:14:39,551 --> 01:14:41,756
It's okay, it's okay,
everything's gonna be fine.

731
01:14:44,255 --> 01:14:47,712
# Will you walk into my parlor #

732
01:14:47,712 --> 01:14:50,330
# Said the spider to the fly #

733
01:14:51,775 --> 01:14:53,055
You're not my mother.

734
01:14:53,055 --> 01:14:54,111
Yes, she is.

735
01:14:54,111 --> 01:14:56,735
I am, Bryan,
I am your mother.

736
01:14:56,735 --> 01:14:58,430
It's time you joined
your real family.

737
01:14:58,430 --> 01:14:59,423
No.

738
01:14:59,423 --> 01:15:01,056
Don't you want to live
for ever, Bryan?

739
01:15:01,056 --> 01:15:03,295
Faith, we can all get
what we want here tonight.

740
01:15:03,295 --> 01:15:04,953
All I want is my baby back.

741
01:15:09,950 --> 01:15:11,860
Share the gift
of the afterlife with me.

742
01:15:12,991 --> 01:15:15,129
You're not part of the final step.

743
01:15:28,958 --> 01:15:29,973
Come here.

744
01:15:35,742 --> 01:15:36,734
Johnny, come on.

745
01:15:36,734 --> 01:15:38,590
You don't have
to be scared, Bryan.

746
01:15:38,590 --> 01:15:40,150
We're all meant to be together.

747
01:15:41,277 --> 01:15:44,990
I just want to hold
my baby boy again.

748
01:15:44,990 --> 01:15:45,982
Come with us.

749
01:15:50,109 --> 01:15:51,419
Get off!

750
01:15:53,534 --> 01:15:54,908
Everything's gonna be okay.

751
01:16:06,270 --> 01:16:07,415
Uh!

752
01:16:12,157 --> 01:16:13,269
Go, go, go, go.

753
01:16:28,157 --> 01:16:29,531
- We can go around.
- Okay.

754
01:16:31,708 --> 01:16:32,722
Now.

755
01:17:05,852 --> 01:17:07,259
Do you still have
those matches?

756
01:17:07,292 --> 01:17:08,371
Yeah.

757
01:17:09,628 --> 01:17:10,773
Okay.

758
01:17:15,419 --> 01:17:16,695
Now, get ready to run.

759
01:17:19,546 --> 01:17:20,539
- Ready?
- Yeah.

760
01:17:20,539 --> 01:17:21,521
Now!

761
01:17:28,090 --> 01:17:29,306
- Guy, come on.
- Spray him.

762
01:17:29,306 --> 01:17:30,234
Come on!

763
01:18:05,146 --> 01:18:06,291
Let's go!

764
01:18:20,218 --> 01:18:21,265
Go!

765
01:18:28,153 --> 01:18:30,389
The final step!

766
01:18:46,808 --> 01:18:48,150
Let her go!

767
01:18:54,584 --> 01:18:56,209
Good night, little brother.

768
01:19:07,448 --> 01:19:08,658
Emma.

769
01:19:53,110 --> 01:19:54,934
Please stop,
stop, let me go!

770
01:19:54,934 --> 01:19:57,334
Please don't do this!

771
01:19:57,334 --> 01:19:59,862
Don't, please, please,
please, let me go!

772
01:19:59,862 --> 01:20:01,846
Please like...
you don't have to do this.

773
01:20:01,846 --> 01:20:03,446
You don't have to do this,
it's not me.

774
01:20:03,446 --> 01:20:04,854
It's not me, it's the fifth nail!

775
01:20:04,854 --> 01:20:06,646
Daniel understands.
Please?

776
01:20:06,646 --> 01:20:08,470
You're making a mistake.

777
01:20:08,470 --> 01:20:10,646
Stop, stop!

778
01:20:10,646 --> 01:20:13,365
Mom, Mom, let me go,
you don't need to do this.

779
01:20:13,365 --> 01:20:16,054
You're making a mistake,
please stop.

780
01:20:16,054 --> 01:20:17,334
Benjamin.

781
01:20:17,334 --> 01:20:20,022
Ben-- Dad, please,
Dad, please just stop!

782
01:20:20,022 --> 01:20:21,622
I can help you,
you don't have to do this.

783
01:20:21,622 --> 01:20:22,709
Just let me go!

784
01:20:22,709 --> 01:20:24,693
Please, please, just stop--

785
01:20:28,021 --> 01:20:29,493
Please?

786
01:20:29,493 --> 01:20:31,894
You don't have to do this.

787
01:20:31,894 --> 01:20:35,276
Mom, just let me go,
let me go, I can help you.

788
01:20:37,749 --> 01:20:38,868
Oh, God.

789
01:20:38,868 --> 01:20:40,789
Emma!

790
01:20:40,789 --> 01:20:43,210
Help, please, somebody!

791
01:20:45,653 --> 01:20:49,301
Just stop, you don't have to do this,
I can save you.

792
01:20:49,301 --> 01:20:51,604
Please, I know how to help you.

793
01:20:51,604 --> 01:20:54,229
I know what to do to save you,
just-- just let me go.

794
01:20:54,229 --> 01:20:55,253
You don't have to do this.

795
01:20:55,253 --> 01:20:57,460
It's the fifth nail, it's not me.
Please?

796
01:20:57,460 --> 01:20:59,252
Please, please, no, no!

797
01:20:59,252 --> 01:21:01,045
Just stop!

798
01:21:01,045 --> 01:21:02,388
Oh, God!

799
01:21:02,388 --> 01:21:04,885
Please don't, please, please,
please, Mom?

800
01:21:04,885 --> 01:21:06,707
Please, stop.

801
01:21:07,413 --> 01:21:09,779
No, no, please, Mom,
let me go.

802
01:21:09,812 --> 01:21:10,739
Let me go.

803
01:21:14,164 --> 01:21:15,888
Oh, God!

804
01:22:00,883 --> 01:22:02,159
Emma, look out!

805
01:22:04,019 --> 01:22:05,330
Emma!

806
01:22:05,330 --> 01:22:06,258
No!

807
01:23:09,041 --> 01:23:10,055
Emma.

808
01:23:14,449 --> 01:23:15,758
I can't believe you're okay.

809
01:23:16,336 --> 01:23:18,256
Oh, you saved my life.

810
01:23:18,256 --> 01:23:19,369
I'm sorry.

811
01:23:20,304 --> 01:23:21,711
Emma's gone.

812
01:23:25,968 --> 01:23:27,375
Emma's gone?

813
01:23:29,264 --> 01:23:30,475
Daniel?

814
01:23:36,176 --> 01:23:37,582
Hey, boy.

815
01:23:53,359 --> 01:23:55,399
No more suffering.

816
01:24:01,935 --> 01:24:03,341
Save my soul, Bryan.

817
01:24:05,295 --> 01:24:06,539
I can't.

818
01:24:07,375 --> 01:24:08,652
It has to end.

819
01:24:09,807 --> 01:24:11,400
Please don't leave me alone.

820
01:24:17,102 --> 01:24:18,085
I'm sorry.

821
01:25:08,046 --> 01:25:09,833
So, how about you tellin' me
what happened here?

822
01:25:12,812 --> 01:25:14,154
I wouldn't even know
where to start.

823
01:25:17,453 --> 01:25:20,525
Sheriff Depford was
a good friend of mine.

824
01:25:20,525 --> 01:25:24,525
And after his retirement, I kept him
in the loop on the Conroy case.

825
01:25:24,525 --> 01:25:28,205
He shared the evidence
and he gave me his theories.

826
01:25:28,205 --> 01:25:29,252
And I'll tell ya...

827
01:25:30,284 --> 01:25:32,805
I thought
he'd completely lost it.

828
01:25:33,773 --> 01:25:35,245
He wasn't crazy.

829
01:25:37,420 --> 01:25:39,852
Well, why don't we get you
to the hospital

830
01:25:39,852 --> 01:25:42,470
and then we can iron out this story
before you talk to anybody else.

831
01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:45,285
Thank you.

832
01:25:47,725 --> 01:25:50,764
I'll tell you, kid, I just want to get
you on your way home, that's all.

833
01:25:54,380 --> 01:25:55,395
I am home.

